<subSubSection id="BA08223FC122E9C264712AA527D0A4C2" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="274D956559659A44C9900D00BCD9691A" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C84AA5F71E8617060675169703E189E3" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
The genus name is derived from the word 
<normalizedToken id="22992749EF38CADAA970F5D189C18F3E" originalValue="“Darwin”">&quot;Darwin&quot;</normalizedToken>
in honor of Charles Darwin who collected the beetle during the voyage of the Beagle. The name is masculine.
</paragraph>
